KANO – Jamila Muhammad Sani, wife to Abdulmalik Tanko, prime suspect on the alleged murder of Hanifa Abubakar was set free by a court on Friday. Jamila Musa, 30 was docked for allegedly concealing a kidnap victim in her matrimonial home for a period of 5 days. The Magistrate court presided over by Chief Magistrate, Muhammad Jibril discharged the defendant after a trial within a trial proved that she has no case to answer. Court Reserves Ruling On Bail Application For Adedoyin, Six… Court Remands Siblings For Attempted Murder Jamila testified had on Thursday against her husband in the ongoing trial at the Kano State High Court. In her submission, Jamila told the court that her embattled husband had told her that the late Hanifa was a daughter to his staff who secured a job in Saudi Arabia and went to Abuja to process a visa when he brought her home. Under cross-examination, Jamila said she didn’t know anything about Hanifa’s death until when the Security Operatives stormed their house. The defence counsel, Barrister Lamido Abba Soron Dinki had informed the court that the investigation revealed that Jamila has no knowledge of the allegation of kidnapping, concealing, torture and killing by her husband and his two co-defendants. The highly elated Jamila expressed happiness soon as the magistrate discharged her at the end of the proceedings.